# Fluff Date: 2026-03-08 20:16:39
<overview>
<p>The Koi Heavy Transport is a large wing-in-ground-effect cargo vehicle designed and manufactured by Wakazashi Enterprises for the Draconis Combine's domestic transport market. Introduced in 3056, the Koi was created to address a recognized gap in planetary logistics on Combine worlds where DropShip transport is economically impractical for routine cargo movement. Wakazashi positioned the design for the civilian sector, emphasizing cargo capacity and long-range overwater transit over military utility.</p><p>The Koi's enormous two-hundred-forty-ton frame carries over one hundred twenty tons of reconfigurable cargo, and its fusion powerplant provides operational range limited only by crew endurance. Coordinator Theodore Kurita's economic modernization reforms drove demand for precisely this kind of high-capacity domestic transport, and the Koi quickly became a fixture of commercial logistics across the Draconis Combine and neighboring states.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Koi's most significant asset is its cargo flexibility. The main bay accommodates standard freight containers, infantry formations, wheeled and tracked vehicles, or even a single BattleMech, with quick-release flotation tanks and powerful pumps enabling rapid reconfiguration between load types. This versatility makes the Koi useful for planetary militia and light garrison commands that lack dedicated combat transport assets.</p><p>Wing-in-ground-effect movement gives the Koi effectively unlimited overwater range. Its amphibious chassis modification allows bay doors to be opened while the vehicle is afloat without risk of flooding, enabling loading and unloading from open coastlines or shallow anchorages with no port infrastructure required. Cruise speed over water is modest, though flank speed is adequate for emergency maneuver away from a threat.</p><p>The Koi's limitations are considerable for any military context. It carries no weapons, relying entirely on escorts for protection. All WiGE vehicles are inherently vulnerable to conventional aircraft and aerospace fighters, and the Koi's enormous radar profile makes evasion impossible. Its large size means combat damage while carrying a full load risks catastrophic loss of both cargo and vehicle. The design is also exposed to ground fire if forced to transit near hostile positions at low altitude.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Koi Heavy Transport serves primarily as a commercial cargo vehicle throughout the Draconis Combine, operated by trading houses, planetary governments, and militia logistics commands. Export units are found across the Inner Sphere wherever cost-effective long-range overwater cargo movement is needed. The design is unarmed and unsuited for frontline service, but its enormous payload makes it an indispensable asset in rear-area logistics and disaster relief operations. On Tabayama, the Hunters International collective operates a large fleet for hunting and agricultural transport across the world's extensive croplands.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>Wakazashi Enterprises developed the Koi against a backdrop of rising commercial demand across the Draconis Combine's interior worlds. Coordinator Theodore Kurita's economic modernization program, begun in the decades before the Clan Invasion, created pressure on domestic logistics networks that existing transport infrastructure struggled to meet. Wakazashi, already an established producer of military WiGE vehicles, recognized an opportunity in the civilian cargo market and committed development resources to a purpose-built design.</p><p>The Koi entered production at the Wakazashi facility on Dover in 3056 and found ready buyers among planetary governments, trading houses, and militia commands throughout the Combine. Its combination of payload and aquatic flexibility made it especially attractive on worlds with extensive coastlines or inland waterways. The Hunters International collective on Tabayama adopted the design early, using it to move hunting parties and equipment across the world's vast croplands far faster than ground vehicles could manage.</p><p>The commercial success of the Koi attracted unwanted attention. In 3061, a factory fire on Dover halted production for three months. Wakazashi executives publicly accused Pesht Motors, the Combine's primary manufacturer of civilian transports, of deliberate sabotage. An investigation confirmed the fire was arson, but no definitive evidence linking Pesht Motors to the incident was produced. Relations between the two corporations have remained strained since, and the disruption gave Wakazashi internal justification to shift some research and development activity off Dover. That decision would later shape how the Koi's military derivatives were developed.</p><p>The Koi has continued as a commercial backbone for planetary logistics in the Draconis Combine, with export units reaching neighboring states. Militia commands short on dedicated transport WiGEs have repeatedly pressed civilian Koi units into emergency service during periods of conflict, a role for which the vehicle was not designed but has proven capable of fulfilling.</p>
</history>

